	Imeris: Pathetic man. Relying on others down to the end, I see.
	Imeris: Do you have no words of your own that are not fed to you?
	Imeris: Are you but a mouthpiece for others?
	Imeris: How I could have been so blind as to believe in you, I will never understand.
	Imeris: The strength to trust in Our Lady's power, and the knowledge of her scriptures.
	Imeris: All I am today, I am because of you.
	Imeris: Because of what you taught me.
	Imeris: I have become myself, and my self is holy, even if you lack the eyes to see it.
	Imeris: And your damnation is your fault alone.
	Linnaeus is mute with rage.
	He bares his teeth, eyes crazed, unable to draw out a single clever word in response.
	You fall into silence, satisfied.
	There is nothing more to say.
	[signal arg="EnemyTurn"]
	set {currentRound} += 1
