	You clasp your hands and look at the face of the goddess. When you lower your gaze, Linnaeus's furious eyes look back.
	Linnaeus: Now you pray?
	Linnaeus: Do you think it will save you?
	Linnaeus: It is far too late for that.
	Linnaeus: She does not love you any longer.
	You close your eyes, lower your head, and begin to mumble your prayer.
	Linnaeus snarls.
	Imeris: O' Goddess,
	Imeris: Save my soul.
